options(repos = c(CRAN = "https://cran.r-project.org/"))
install.packages("FNN")
## 
## The downloaded binary packages are in
##  /var/folders/9r/_pblp2qx5td0165fzjbvlt680000gn/T//RtmpAw86fk/downloaded_packages
library(MASS) # for truehist
library(FNN) # for knn.reg
library(tidyverse)
# Set parameters
train_sample_size <- 500
rep_num <- 1000
p_max <- 10
sigma_val <- c(0, 1) 

# Define the true function f(X)
Y <- function(X) X[,1]

# Initialize a dataframe to store results
results <- data.frame()
# Main loop for different number of dimensions, methods and sigma
for (p in 1:p_max) {
  for (sigma in sigma_val) {
    for (method in c("lm", "knn")) {
      epe_values <- numeric(rep_num)
      
      for (i in 1:rep_num) {
        # Training data
        X_train <- matrix(runif(train_sample_size * p,-1, 1), ncol = p)
        Y_train <- Y(X_train) + rnorm(train_sample_size, 0, sigma)
        
        # Predict at x0 = 0
        X0 <- matrix(0, ncol = p, nrow = 1)
        if (method == "lm") {
          X_df <- data.frame(Y_train, X_train)
          colnames(X_df) <- c("Y", paste0("V", 1:p))
          # Name the variables for consistency
          model <- lm(Y~ ., data = X_df) 
          X0_df <- data.frame(t(rep(0, p))) # Create a data frame with p columns
          colnames(X0_df) <- paste0("V", 1:p) 
          Y_pred <- predict(model, newdata = X0_df)
          } else if (method == "knn") {
          Y_pred <- knn.reg(train = X_train, test = X0, y = Y_train, k = 1)$pred
        }
        # Compute the error
        error <- (Y(X0)- Y_pred)^2
        epe_values[i] <- error
      }
      # Store the results
      results <- rbind(results, data.frame(
        p = p,
        sigma = sigma,
        method = method,
        epe = mean(epe_values)
      ))
    }
  }
}

## [1] "Test MSE: 2945.3835193228"
# Identify significant variables
coefs <- summary(model)$coefficients[-1,] # Without the intercept
sig_vars <- names(coefs)[coefs[,4] < 0.05]

# Check if any variable is significant
if (length(sig_vars) > 0) {
  # Prepare data for smaller model
  smaller_data <- as.data.frame(train_x)[, sig_vars, drop = FALSE]
  
  # Fit smaller model
  formula <- as.formula(paste("train_y ~", paste(sig_vars, collapse = " + ")))
  smaller_model <- lm(formula, data = cbind(train_y, smaller_data))
 
   # Evaluate in-sample fit for smaller model
  pred_train_small <- predict(smaller_model, newdata = smaller_data)
  mse_train_small <- mean((pred_train_small- train_y)^2)
  print(paste("Training MSE (smaller model):", mse_train_small))
  
  # Evaluate on test data for smaller model
  smaller_test_data <- as.data.frame(test_x)[, sig_vars, drop = FALSE]
  pred_test_small <- predict(smaller_model, newdata = smaller_test_data)
  mse_test_small <- mean((pred_test_small- test_y)^2)
  print(paste("Test MSE (smaller model):", mse_test_small))
  
  # Compare models using F-test
  print(anova(model, smaller_model))
} else {
  print("No significant variables found at 5% significance level.")
}
## [1] "No significant variables found at 5% significance level."

library(lars)
library(MuMIn)
data(diabetes)
X <- data.frame(diabetes$x)
y <- diabetes$y

set.seed(2)

# Training and testing sets
train_indices <- sample(1:nrow(X), 400)
train_data <- data.frame(cbind(y = y[train_indices], X[train_indices, ]))
test_data <- data.frame(cbind(y = y[-train_indices], X[-train_indices, ]))

# Fit the full model on the training data
full_model <- lm(y~., data = train_data)
# Perform stepwise regression
step_model <- step(full_model, direction = "backward")

# Best subset selection using the dredge function from MuMIn package
full_model_glm <- glm(y~., data = train_data, na.action = na.fail)
models <- dredge(full_model_glm, rank = "AIC")
## Fixed term is "(Intercept)"
best_model <- get.models(models, subset = 1)[[1]]

# Function to compute MSE
compute_mse <- function(model, data) {
  pred <- predict(model, newdata = data)
  mse <- mean((data$y- pred)^2)
  return(mse)
}

# In-sample and out-of-sample MSE for each model
mse_results <- data.frame(
  Model = c("Full Model", "Stepwise", "Best Subset"),
  In_Sample_MSE = c(
    compute_mse(full_model, train_data),
    compute_mse(step_model, train_data),
    compute_mse(best_model, train_data)
  ),
  Out_of_Sample_MSE = c(
    compute_mse(full_model, test_data),
    compute_mse(step_model, test_data),
    compute_mse(best_model, test_data)
  )
)
# Extract coefficients
coeff_results <- data.frame(
  Model = c("Full Model", "Stepwise", "Best Subset"),
  Coefficients = c(
    paste(coef(full_model), collapse = ", "),
    paste(coef(step_model), collapse = ", "),
    paste(coef(best_model), collapse = ", ")
  )
)
# Print the MSE results
print(mse_results)

  data = Wage)

# Comparison of Models with ANOVA

library(MASS)
# Forward Stagewise function
forward_stagewise <- function(x,
                              y,
                              tol = 10 ^ -3,
                              max_steps = 10000,
                              epsilon) {
  if (!is.matrix(x))
    stop("Input x must be a matrix")
  if (nrow(x) != length(y))
    stop("Number of rows of x must be equal to length of y")
  if (!is.numeric(x) |
      !is.numeric(y))
    stop("X and y must be numeric inputs")
  
  n <- nrow(x)
  p <- ncol(x)
  
  x <- scale(x, center = TRUE, scale = FALSE)
  y <- scale(y, center = TRUE, scale = FALSE)
  
  Beta <- rep(0, p)
  Beta_path <- Beta
  
  cor <- 1
  steps <- 0
  
  while (cor > tol & steps < max_steps)
  {
    residuals <- y - x %*% Beta
    IP <- crossprod(x, residuals) # proportional to correl (would be n*correl if standardized)
    i <- which.max(abs(IP))
    
    coefficient <- lm(residuals ~ x[, i], data = as.data.frame(x)) #new line
    coefficient <- coef(coefficient)[2]
    
    
    Beta[i] <- Beta[i] + epsilon * coefficient #changed: coefficient instead of sign!
    Beta_path <- rbind(Beta_path, Beta_path = Beta)
    
    steps <- steps + 1
    cor <- max(abs(cor(x, residuals)))
    
  }
  list(Beta = Beta,
       Beta_path = Beta_path,
       steps = steps)
}


# Show how function works with less predictors
set.seed(123)
n <- 100
p <- 10
X <- matrix(rnorm(n * p), n, p)

beta <- c(1.5, -2, 0.7, rep(0, p - 3))  # Only first three predictors are relevant
y <- X %*% beta + rnorm(n)

x <- forward_stagewise(
  x = X,
  y = y,
  tol = sqrt(.Machine$double.eps),
  epsilon = 0.01,
  max_steps = 10 ^ 5
)

# using our data (300 observations, 31 predictors, would take very long to reach the tolerance
# and then doing this 50 times would take forever, hence using bigger tolerance)

#Simulation itself
set.seed(666)
n_sims <- 50
# fix fixed values
N <- 300
p <- 31
corr <- 0.85

Sigma <- matrix(corr, nrow = p, ncol = p)
diag(Sigma) <- 1

final <- matrix(0, nrow = n_sims, ncol = 2)
colnames(final) <- c("Norm error for FSW", "Norm error for BSS")
for (s in 1:n_sims){
  # set up random values
  X <- mvrnorm(n = N,
               mu = rep(0, p),
               Sigma = Sigma)
  
  true_beta <- c(rnorm(10, mean = 0, sd = 0.6), rep(0, p - 10))
  epsilon <- rnorm(N, mean = 0, sd = 2.5)
  
  y <- X %*% true_beta + epsilon
  
  reg <- forward_stagewise(X,
                           y,
                           tol = 10 ^ -2,
                           max_steps = 10 ^ 4,
                           epsilon = 0.1)
  
  # error for stagewise
  normerror_fwd <- sum((reg$Beta - true_beta) ^ 2)
  
  data <- as.data.frame(cbind(y, X))
  
  models <- regsubsets(V1 ~ .,
                       data = data,
                       nbest = 1,
                       nvmax = p,
                       method = "exhaustive")
  results <- summary(models)
  
  coef <- coef(models, which.min(results$bic))
  coef <- coef[-1]
  
  result_bs <- results$which[which.min(results$bic), ]
  result_bs <- as.numeric(result_bs[-1])
  
  for (i in 1:length(result_bs))
  {
    if (result_bs[i] == 1)
    {
      result_bs[i] <- coef[1]
      coef <- coef[-1]
    }
    
  }
  normerror_best <- sum((result_bs - true_beta) ^ 2)
  
  final[s, ] <- cbind(normerror_fwd, normerror_best)
}
